The article provides an agenda and speakers for the upcoming United State of Women Summit, which will be held on June 14, 2016, at the Walter E. Washington Convention Center in Washington, DC. The summit will focus on various topics including violence against women, health and wellness, economic opportunity, entrepreneurship and innovation, education, civic engagement, leadership and visibility. There will be plenary sessions and solutions seminars featuring speakers from different sectors including government officials, activists, actors, CEOs, and advocates. The summit will conclude with a conversation between the First Lady and Oprah Winfrey, followed by closing remarks from Valerie Jarrett and Tina Tchen.